d 'XTHKRCOINT': module to perform Hadri-Kurozumi-Rao panel cointegration test with the null of cointegration
d
d	xthkrcoint implements the panel cointegration tests of
d Hadri, Kurozumi and Rao (2015, Econometrics Journal).  The
d distinctive	 features of the test are:	  1. The null
d hypothesis is cointegration for every unit; the alternative is
d that at least one unit is not cointegrated.	       This is the
d natural null when the researcher wishes to establish a long-run
d relationship, and it complements the more	     common
d no-cointegration-null tests (xtcointtest).	    2. The
d asymptotics hold with N fixed and T large, so the test suits
d typical macroeconomic and financial panels where N is 	
d small relative to T. No estimation of the number of common
d factors is required.	      3. Arbitrary cross-section dependence
d (weak or strong, including common factors and cross-unit
d cointegration) is mopped up	       nonparametrically through
d the long-run variance of the pooled autocovariances, in the
d spirit of Driscoll-Kraay. The 	 pooled statistic is
d therefore asymptotically standard normal and no bootstrap
d critical values are needed.	     4. Serial correlation is
d handled by dynamic OLS (DOLS) — the cointegrating regression is
d augmented with leads and lags of	    Dx — and a bias
d correction removes the finite-sample negative bias of the
d autocovariance statistic (which otherwise	     makes the test
d conservative).    The command reports the pooled statistic
d S{sub:K} (uncorrected) and S~{sub:K} (bias-corrected), each with
d a one-sided	 (upper-tail) p-value, a decision at the 5% level,
d and a per-unit breakdown showing which cross-sections drive a
d rejection.	With graph it draws a two-panel diagnostics
d dashboard. 
d
d KW: panel data
d KW: unit root tests
d KW: cointegration
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260708
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xthkrcoint.ado
f xthkrcoint.sthlp
f xthkrcoint_postestimation.sthlp
f xthkrcoint_example.do
